-- BrasilAgro, Ecopetrol, Petrobras, Redecard: Latin America Equity Preview
-- Alexander Ragir
-- 2010-06-28T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/brasilagro-ecopetrol-petrobras-redecard-latin-america-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Latin American trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous
close.  
 The  MSCI Latin America Index  dropped 1.5 percent to
3,874.38. In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-
traded class of stock.  
 Brazil  
 Cia. Brasileira de Propriedades Agricolas SA  (AGRO3 BS):
The agricultural company said Credit Suisse Hedging-Griffo
Corretora de Valores SA now owns almost 8 percent of its common
shares, according to a regulatory filing. BrasilAgro fell 7.1
percent to 8.50 reais.  
 Cia. de Bebidas das Americas (AMBV4 BS): Latin America’s
largest brewer, known as AmBev, will announce this week a 152
million reais ($85.4 million) investment in a plant in Rio
Grande do Sul state, Folha de S.Paulo reported, citing Milton
Seligman, vice president for corporate affairs. The stock rose
0.9 percent to 186.73 reais.  
 Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BS): Brazil’s state-
controlled oil company’s total production of oil and natural gas
rose 2.1 percent in May from a year earlier. Output climbed to
2.599 million barrels of oil equivalent a day in Brazil and
abroad, from 2.547 million barrels in May 2009, Petrobras said.  
 Separately, the company agreed to pay 1 million reais to
settle a case with the nation’s securities regulator. Petrobras
gained 1.5 percent to 27.91 reais.  
 Redecard SA  (RDCD3 BS): The payment processing company
named Marcio de Andrade Schettini chairman of the board,
replacing Joaquim Francisco de Castro Neto, the company said in
a regulatory filing. Redecard rose 3 percent to 28.11 reais.  
 Colombia  
 Ecopetrol SA  (ECOPETL CB): The Colombian state-owned oil
producer targeting expansion in the U.S. Gulf of Mexico and
Brazil may consider bidding for exploration blocks in
neighboring Peru, Ecopetrol Chief Executive Officer Javier
Gutierrez said in an interview. The stock rose 0.2 percent to
2,775 pesos.  
